      "description": "This E92 M3 is a formidable example of high-revving German engineering, powered by the S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. The powerplant features individual throttle bodies and a 12.0:1 compression ratio, screaming to an 8,400 RPM redline. This chassis is equipped with the M-DCT dual-clutch transmission for instantaneous gear changes and a limited-slip M-variable differential for optimal torque distribution. Suspension dynamics are managed via Electronic Damper Control (EDC), providing exceptional turn-in and mid-corner stability. Maintenance is up to date with rod bearing service and throttle actuator replacements already documented, ensuring the mechanical integrity of this high-performance platform.",
